Name: Painted relief with a hieroglyph
Description: Fragment of raised relief plaster, delicately painted, with part of the hieroglyph in the form of a jar-rack, used in the Egyptian word 'khent' 'to the fore of' (in epithets of gods 'foremost of' such-and-such a place). The style indicates a high status tomb of the New Kingdom, in the Theban area.
